{"type":"TEXT_MESSAGE_CONTENT","timestamp":1775718991,"rawEvent":{"content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me now understand the approach:\n\n**The FetchPixelStats API** will be a new method on `IReplayController` that leverages the existing GPU counter mechanism (specifically `SamplesPassed` and `PSInvocations`) but returns a simpler, more focused struct. However, for the **overdraw distribution** feature, we need a different approach - we can't get per-pixel overdraw counts from GPU counters alone (they only give totals per drawcall).\n\nFor overdraw distribution, we need to use a **stencil-based approach**: render each drawcall with stencil increment, then read back the stencil buffer to count how many pixels have each stencil value. This is a well-known technique.\n\nLet me now plan the implementation and start coding. The key files to modify are:\n\n1. **`data_types.h`** - Add `PixelEventStats` and `OverdrawDistribution` structs\n2. **`renderdoc_replay.h`** - Add `FetchPixelStats` to `IReplayController` interface\n3. **`replay_controller.h`** - Add declaration in `ReplayController` class\n4. **`replay_controller.cpp`** - Add implementation\n5. **`replay_driver.h`** - Add to `IRemoteDriver` interface\n6. **`d3d11_replay.h`** - Add D3D11 declaration\n7. **`d3d11_counters.cpp`** - Add D3D11 implementation\n8. **`d3d12_replay.h`** - Add D3D12 declaration\n9. **`d3d12_counters.cpp`** - Add D3D12 implementation\n10. **`replay_proxy.h`** / **`replay_proxy.cpp`** - Add proxy support\n11. **`renderdoc_serialise.inl`** - Add serialization\n12. **`renderdoc.i`** - Add SWIG bindings\n\nLet me also check GL and Vulkan replay headers since they also implement IRemoteDriver:"}}

