{"type":"TEXT_MESSAGE_CONTENT","timestamp":1775719025,"rawEvent":{"content":"Now I have a complete understanding. Since `FetchPixelStats` can be implemented purely at the `ReplayController` level (composing existing `FetchCounters`), I don't need to modify the driver interfaces at all. This is the cleanest approach.\n\nFor overdraw distribution, I'll implement a stencil-based approach at the `ReplayController` level too - by using the existing `RenderOverlay` mechanism or by directly using the replay infrastructure.\n\nActually, let me reconsider. The simplest and most effective approach is:\n\n1. **`FetchPixelStats`** - Uses existing `FetchCounters` to get `SamplesPassed`, `PSInvocations`, `RasterizedPrimitives`, `EventGPUDuration` per event. This gives `pixelTouched` (= `SamplesPassed`).\n\n2. **Overdraw distribution** - For per-pixel overdraw, we need to replay each drawcall with stencil increment and read back. This is complex. A simpler approach: for each event, `PSInvocations / SamplesPassed` gives average overdraw. But for actual distribution, we'd need a custom approach.\n\nLet me implement the practical approach: `FetchPixelStats` at the `ReplayController` level, and for overdraw distribution, provide an estimation based on counter ratios. For actual per-pixel overdraw distribution of a specific drawcall range, we can implement a separate method that uses the stencil approach.\n\nLet me start implementing. I'll add the struct to `data_types.h`, the interface to `renderdoc_replay.h`, the implementation to `replay_controller.cpp`, and the SWIG bindings."}}

